pain, changes in bowel motions, or weight loss. He is otherwise well with no medical history or current medications. He smokes 20 cigarettes a day and has done so for 20 years. The physical examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA barium swallow study is arranged (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of this patient\u0027s presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Para-oesophageal hernia","Sliding hiatus hernia","Carcinoma of the cardia","Achalasia","Peptic stricture"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe contrast shows a massively dilated oesophagus, with a sump and a \u0027bird\u0027s beak\u0027 appearance at the cardia. There is a large residue of food particles in the sump. Together with the characteristic history, this contrast confirms the diagnosis of end-stage \u003Cstrong\u003Eachalasia\u003C/strong\u003E. Not all patients have symptoms of heartburn and weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epara-oesophageal hiatus hernia\u003C/strong\u003E will show a portion of the gastric fundus herniating through the diaphragm on barium swallow. These hernias are generally asymptomatic until complications such as incarceration or gastric volvulus occur.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Esliding hiatus hernia\u003C/strong\u003E is also often asymptomatic. It is diagnosed by the presence of a mucosal B ring \u0026gt;2cm above the diaphragmatic impression on barium swallow. This is reducible with a patient in an erect position.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA barium swallow may be able to demonstrate strictures and luminal compression of the oesophagus caused by masses, such as a \u003Cstrong\u003Epeptic stricture\u003C/strong\u003E, or \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarcinoma of the cardia\u003C/strong\u003E; however, these are not present in this patient\u0027s barium swallow. Since the advent of proton pump inhibitors, peptic strictures have become very uncommon and it would be unusual to get such massive oesophageal dilatation above such a stricture. Most patients with oesophageal malignancy have rapidly progressing symptoms and the length of history in this case virtually excludes such a diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Achalasia is characterised by bird\u0027s beak sign and oesophageal dilatation on barium swallow."],"references":["Vaezi MF, Pandolfino JE, Yadlapati RH, et al. ACG Clinical Guidelines: Diagnosis and Management of Achalasia. Am J Gastroenterol. 2020;115(9):1393-1411. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32773454/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85559"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1652"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17779"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17779","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17779"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4c357e53-a27d-4e8a-80d4-4e6ece8fd864.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4c357e53-a27d-4e8a-80d4-4e6ece8fd864.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":667,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85559"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-19T14:50:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-19T14:51:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1652"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103095"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","i